## Context

Transformers.js already defines `AutoModelForImageTextToText` in `src/models.js` (line 8736), mapping to 11 vision-language models (Florence2, LLaVA, SmolVLM, Qwen2VL, etc.). However, there is no corresponding pipeline class or `SUPPORTED_TASKS` entry for `"image-text-to-text"` yet. This plan adds the full pipeline plumbing so users can call `pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft')` with an image + text prompt and get `[{ generated_text: "..." }]` back.

---

## File to Modify

**`src/pipelines.js`** — all four changes below are in this single file.

---

## Change 1 — Add import for `AutoModelForImageTextToText` (line ~43)

Insert `AutoModelForImageTextToText,` into the existing `import { ... } from './models.js'` block, after `AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction` (currently line 43).

**Before (lines 41–45):**
```js
    AutoModelForImageToImage,
    AutoModelForDepthEstimation,
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    PreTrainedModel,
} from './models.js';
```

**After:**
```js
    AutoModelForImageToImage,
    AutoModelForDepthEstimation,
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,
    PreTrainedModel,
} from './models.js';
```

---

## Change 2 — Add `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class (after line 2779)

Insert **immediately after** `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` closes (line 2779) and before the `VocoderOptions` typedef block (line 2782).

The new block follows the exact typedef → JSDoc → class pattern of both reference implementations:

```js
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Process an image with a text prompt.
 * @param {ImageInput} image The image to process.
 * @param {string} text The text prompt describing what to do with the image.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments to pass along to the generate method of the model.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput>} An array of objects containing the generated text(s).
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */

/**
 * Image-text-to-text pipeline using any `AutoModelForImageTextToText`.
 * This pipeline accepts an image and a text prompt, and generates text based on both inputs.
 * It can be used for tasks such as image captioning with a custom prompt, visual question
 * answering, or any other image-conditioned text generation task.
 *
 * **Example:** Describe an image with `onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft`.
 * ```javascript
 * const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft');
